{"author":{"id":"6bb94ae2d5a59e66e1b5226cb7c83f5e6be898f8e834fe311644ad3320becc80"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1773067235,"nonce":"yOzygMaexZVBgTrFJchH8KYhi3M=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s7xKRbY","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/7766","origin":"github"},"title":"Tools request: Github neighbors and prim","message":"Dear Galaxy builders,\n\nthank you very much for your work in getting the Find Unique Regions (fur) tool from target and neighbor genomes built into Galaxy!\n(now at https://usegalaxy.eu/?tool_id=fur )\n\nThe authors of fur have 2 associated sofware tools available at Github that work closely together with fur:\n\nneighbors to identify target and neighbor genomes for marker discovery:\nhttps://github.com/EvolBioInf/neighbors\n\nand prim, a toolshed for designing and testing primers that target unique regions discovered by fur:\nhttps://github.com/EvolBioInf/prim\n\nIt would be great if you could make these two tools also available on Galaxy so that one may go from discovering unique regions in microbes to developing primer pairs detecting those regions in Galaxy,\n\nwith regards,\nPeter van Baarlen,\nHost-Microbe Interactomics group,\nUniversity Wageningen","files":null}]}